The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest paths and cycles in embedded graphs, which are typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of randomized algorithms and analysis of their high-probability time bounds suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of randomized algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.DL). Finally, the study of cycles in graphs and their properties is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT), which is also relevant to this paper.
